building the kernel
- go to project folder, and select a make file to build
- outside the cloned folder, create a new folder for the user code changes.
- new folder has its own makefile, and rules.mk for the project and app.
- project1.mk is copied from project folder in lk.
- makefile is generated using script given in docs. similarly rules.mk is generated using script given in docs. 
- app/hello should be added in project1.mk - this is for adding app/hello folder to get included in compilation.
- rules.mk defines .c files and includes module.mk(from lk)
- APP_START - defines the struct with app name, and places it in the app section
- if .init, and .entry is defined for the app, then kernel would execute those function.
- STATIC_COMMAND_START,STATIC_COMMAND,STATIC_COMMAND_END - this adds a command for the console, and the function mapped to the command, will get executed, whenever this command is passed in console

